  "summary": "Malicious code in react-leaflet-marker-layer (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (7b37a04b363c4392e401d85320c748dab98c13ff46c74624f21aaa70091b8ae6)\nThe package react-leaflet-marker-layer was found to contain malicious code.\n\n## Source: google-open-source-security (306d70c46c0fb0ef8d41b5f8c730d785a321c0576641ef05de403e0276b1e0e8)\nThis package was compromised by the CanisterWorm campaign by the TeamPCP\nthreat actor. The malicious payload establishes persistence as user systemd\nservice and places a backdoor on the infected host. The malware will also\nharvest npm credentials and can autonomously spread.\n",
